This package helps using the command line version of rar and unrar
on linux



Version 0.3: 

Can archive multiple files, but extracting will extract to the current directory
and not respect path info from archive



Install this module like this:

    sudo pip install Lib7zipPython-0.0.x.tar.gz 

(replace x with your version)


You also need 7zip

On ubuntu:

    sudo aptitude install p7zip


Usage example

#!/usr/bin/python
import archive

a = archive.Archive("/home/me/testarchive1.7zip")
a.add_file("/home/me/testfile")
a.run() 
  
